Japan's Mitsui Petrochemical Industries, Mitsui  Engineering and Shipbuilding Co. Ltd. and Marubeni Corp. have won a six  billion yen (58 million dollar) order to build a specialty rubber plant in  China, a Mitsui Petrochemical spokesman said Tuesday.
The spokesman said the ethylene propylene rubber plant ordered by the  Jilin Chemical Industrial Bureau would be the first of its type in China.
The Export-Import of Japan is to finance the construction of the plant,  which is expected to have an annual production capacity of 20,000 tonnes of  rubber for use in automotive parts, he said.
